  "What you're looking for is already where you're looking from. Overthinking slows you down. Simply be.",
  "Many people believe they have the mentality to be successful when, in reality, they don't have the will to take a risk.",
  "Grinding hard even after it benefits me.",
  "If it's in your heart to finish what you started, then finish at all costs.",
  "Until you can affect real positive change in someone else's life, you're just doing okay.",
  "Don't waste time trying to 'figure it all out' because, at the end of the day, it's about doing what satisfies you within.",
  "If you've got a good feeling, hold onto that optimism. It could take you places beyond your imagination.",
  "We spend a lot of time observing what's going on around us, but how much time do we spend observing ourselves?",
  "Be so true to yourself that you'll settle for nothing less than those same qualities in another.",
  "Imagination and love are the greatest gifts we have.",
  "It's not your age that defines your maturity, but your experience.",
  "As a catalyst to your own reality, nothing can stop you but you.",
  "Know the difference between temporary defeat and failure.",
  "Live by an ideal of who you are and what you want.",
  "Realize that you're the tortoise in the race; take a deep breath, smile, and continue steadily along your way.",
  "Things can change overnight, but the journey doesn't happen overnight.",
  "Focusing on being better today than you were yesterday is all that matters.",
  "The process of discovering who you really are starts with knowing who you don't want to be.",
  "There's a time when things come full circle, and you get what you've given.",
  "Many people you will come in contact with will say one thing and do another. Keep an emotional distance and let them be themselves.",
  "One thing's for certain, no matter what happens; life goes on.",
  "Failure doesn't exist, only feedback on how to progress more effectively.",
  "Are you feeling like you're making countless sacrifices for the sake of a greater goal, while everyone else seems to be living carefree? Good, you're right on track for long-term success.",
  "When you realize nobody actually cares outside of what's going on with them, you can zone in and focus on what's most important: YOU.",
